<blockquote>
<p>Samoas, Trefoils and Thin Mints, move over. A new Girl Scout cookie flavor, Raspberry Rally, is in such high demand that, after swiftly selling out online, boxes are now being peddled for far higher prices on resale websites.</p>
<p>Single boxes of the cookies, which have a crispy raspberry-flavored center coated in chocolate, cost from $4 to $7, but they are selling for as much as <a title="" href="https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.ebay.com/itm/275728347952?hash=item4032b0b330:g:mMYAAOSwYTJkBV6G&amp;amdata=enc%3AAQAHAAAA4JffOYfHZpMWavK1m%2FARvf%2Ff1wouE3Nn96vVce8wOr8t%2FZBK3P1mmuPp4aYcqGeUP3fCsmBJHQrgbKGxkMAyIx9t%2BNcc4jQY3GJBAyop1IaDk3kntm8%2B7cx2SZvd8nCMKvTbVkBcH3Y3Z2ZPvUCZ3d6iwFfiyEYHWfLV%2F%2BWEGodoYxWQIvnnnJqSZpHZ4lHL%2FGxPiJJQIiAndUSyrOaJxXphDYttZR3O03YP7XwUr9gNPcry%2FmZy31sFgfiasjZDqd9lTxIhuX1mstxWtSm76i4dCHnye20RL9WVzBnC3qVb%7Ctkp%3ABFBMmLii09dh" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">five times the usual price</a> on the secondary market.</p>
<p>Girl Scouts of the U.S.A. has expressed dismay over the situation. The organization said in a statement that most local Girl Scout troops had sold out of the “extremely popular” Raspberry Rally cookies for the season and emphasized that it was “disappointed” to see unauthorized resales of the flavor…</p>
<p>The Raspberry Rally cookies, which <a title="" href="https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.girlscouts.org/en/footer/press-room/2022-press-announcements/new-raspberry-rally-girl-scout-cookie-joins-nationwide-lineup-for-2023-season.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">first became available late last month</a>, can be bought only online. The cookie is considered a “sister” to the Thin Mint, the top-selling Girl Scout cookie, <a title="" href="https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.girlscouts.org/en/cookies/cookie-flavors/raspberry-rally-cookies.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">according to the Girl Scouts website</a>.</p></blockquote>
<p>Here is <a href="https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.nytimes.com/2023/03/07/business/raspberry-rally-girl-scout-cookies.html" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">more from the NYT</a>, via a loyal <strong>MR</strong> reader.  How about teaching Girl Scouts how to raise the price?</p>
